 Nothing can be claimed, but you must maintain ownership and responsibility for anything you launch.<br>
In several cases at deep sea, the intent of the treaties which say that nobody may interfere with peaceful and openly conducted activities has been interpreted as saying that you have control -if not ownership- of the area immediately around your ship or installation. Things move around, vehicles come and go, and you are responsible, and visitors or others may not interfere. So you may ask another state or NGO to not plop something down right next to your place.<br>
If they insist, there's a whole rats'-nest of ways to settle disputes, so it's a mess of conflicting responsibilities over your activities and anything it might affect, and the requirement to be completely open at all times.<br>
<br>
 The US did sign that treaty, but not the later Moon treaty. (L-5 Society members protested, and carried a letter writing campaign to not let the US sign)<br>
(<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.azstarnet.com/public/nonprofit/tucl5/l5dream.htm">L-5 Society</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> was a precursor of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://nss.org">NSS</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Their purpose, and much of the NSS is to build space colonies and space industry)<br>
<br>
<br>
United Nations Office for Outer Space Affairs (UN-OOSA)<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.oosa.unvienna.org/OOSA/oosa.html">www.oosa.unvienna.org/OOSA/oosa.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p>"Of course power corrupts -what else is it for?" Dominar Rygel XVI of the Hynerian empire</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2063<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/15/02 6:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=314.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: don't worry about it</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Nothing can be claimed<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
